{
  "info": {
    "name": "User Payout Management System",
    "description": "Affiliate-sales payout system: 10% advance payouts, admin reconciliation, and 24h-gated withdrawals with failed-payout recovery. This collection walks through the assignment's own worked example end to end — folders 1 through 4 reproduce the exact ₹12 advance / ₹68 final-payout numbers from the spec, folder 5 exercises the 24h withdrawal gate and Question 2's failed-payout recovery, and folder 6 covers the edge cases documented in the README.\n\n**How to use:** start the server (`bun run dev`), then either click \"Run collection\" for the whole story with automatic assertions, or open folders top to bottom and inspect each response yourself. Every request generates a fresh username on each full run (see the pre-request script on the very first request), so the collection can be re-run any number of times — including inside the same 24h window — without stepping on a previous run's state.\n\nOnly variable you might need to change: `baseUrl` (defaults to `http://localhost:3000`).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "runUser",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "edgeUser",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "saleId1",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "saleId2",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "saleId3",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "withdrawPayoutId1",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "withdrawPayoutId2",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. Health Check",
      "description": "Sanity check that the server is up before running the rest of the collection.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"status is 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test(\"ok is true\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.true; });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1. Seed Sales — Worked Example (3 x Rs 40)",
      "description": "Recreates the assignment's reference data: three pending sales of Rs 40 each for one user/brand. A fresh username is generated here so the whole collection can be re-run safely at any time, including within the same 24h window as a previous run.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Sale 1 (Rs 40)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/sales",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "sales"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{runUser}}\",\n  \"brand\": \"brand_1\",\n  \"earning\": 40\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Fresh user per full run — keeps the 24h withdrawal gate and idempotency",
                  "// guards from colliding with data left over from a previous run.",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"runUser\", \"postman_\" + Date.now());"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"status is 201\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test(\"status is PENDING\", function () { pm.expect(body.status).to.eql(\"PENDING\"); });",
                  "pm.test(\"earning is 40\", function () { pm.expect(body.earning).to.eql(\"40\"); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Sale 2 (Rs 40)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/sales",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "sales"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{runUser}}\",\n  \"brand\": \"brand_1\",\n  \"earning\": 40\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"status is 201\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Sale 3 (Rs 40)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/sales",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "sales"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{runUser}}\",\n  \"brand\": \"brand_1\",\n  \"earning\": 40\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"status is 201\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Advance Payout Job (Business Rule 1)",
      "description": "10% of pending earnings, paid once per sale. Running the job twice proves the idempotency guard.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Run Advance Payout Job",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/jobs/advance-payout",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "jobs",
                "advance-payout"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{runUser}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"status is 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test(\"3 sales processed\", function () { pm.expect(body.salesProcessed).to.eql(3); });",
                  "pm.test(\"total advance is Rs 12.00\", function () { pm.expect(body.totalAdvancePaid).to.eql(\"12.00\"); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Run Advance Payout Job Again (Idempotency Check)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/jobs/advance-payout",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "jobs",
                "advance-payout"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Re-running the job must be a no-op — every sale already got its advance.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{runUser}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"status is 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test(\"0 sales processed (idempotent)\", function () { pm.expect(body.salesProcessed).to.eql(0); });",
                  "pm.test(\"no additional advance paid\", function () { pm.expect(body.totalAdvancePaid).to.eql(\"0.00\"); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Balance After Advance (expect Rs 12.00)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/{{runUser}}/balance",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "users",
                "{{runUser}}",
                "balance"
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"status is 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test(\"balance is 12.00\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().withdrawableBalance).to.eql(\"12.00\"); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Reconciliation (Business Rule 2) - rejected, approved, approved -> Rs 68",
      "description": "Settles the three pending sales exactly as in the assignment's worked example: one rejected (clawback -Rs 4), two approved (+Rs 36 each) -> total final payout Rs 68.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Pending Sales (capture sale ids)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/{{runUser}}/sales?status=pending",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "users",
                "{{runUser}}",
                "sales"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "status",
                  "value": "pending"
                }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"status is 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const sales = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test(\"3 pending sales\", function () { pm.expect(sales.length).to.eql(3); });",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"saleId1\", sales[0].id);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"saleId2\", sales[1].id);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"saleId3\", sales[2].id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Reconcile Sale 1 -> Rejected (adjustment -Rs 4.00)",
